FYI: You can also set filters on a per-Processor basis. Any
CrawlURI instances which fail the filters will merely skip 
that Processor.

So, for example, to have the ARCWriter only archive &quot;http:&quot;
fetches, that portion of the crawl-order might read:

&lt;processor 
  name=&quot;Archiver&quot; 
  class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.basic.ARCWriter&quot;
  next=&quot;Updater&quot;&gt;
 &lt;compression use=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
 &lt;arc-files max-size-bytes=&quot;20000000&quot;/&gt;
 &lt;filter 
   name=&quot;http-only&quot;
   class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.util.URIRegExpFilter&quot;
   regexp=&quot;^http://.*&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/processor&gt;

As some of the legacy ARC tools have problems with anything
other than HTTP records, we&#39;ll often be refraining from
writing the DNS fetches until these incomplatibilities can
be catalogued and corrected.

